<a href="/akira/dtd/2559-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_2559">Be Careful - New Technologies Can Uncover Sensistive Information from Seemingly "Open" Data&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/0-4049">home_builders</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">10 days ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">While we applaud the Administration's open initiatives here, it bears noting that our adversaries possess sophisticated technology that can produce very insightful information from what many might consider "open source", "unclassified" data.  We should proceed very carefully "opening" up government information to the world.    </div>
